place.name: TYNINGHAME
place.gazetteerText: Tynninghame, vil., Whitekirk and Tynninghame par., Haddingtonshire, on river Tyne, 2 miles NE. of East Linton; P.O.; 1 mile NE. is Tynninghame House, seat of the Earl of Haddington. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
